;; evolution runs every 50 ticks for all three agent populations
;; each population selects its fittest members as parents,
;; creates offspring through recombination (immune cells) or directed mutation (bacteria),
;; then replaces the entire old population with the new evolved generation

;; ---- saves the best current genomes without killing any agents ----
;; called once at setup to seed the genome globals before the first evolution cycle
